{
  "doc_id": "52976",
  "text": "Tryptic In-Gel Digest SDS-PAGE bands of interest were digested as described elsewhere [CITATION_1] . In brief, bands of interest were cut out and minced. After destaining with 50% 10 mM NH 4 HCO 3 /50% acetonitrile (ACN) at 55uC and dehydration in 100%ACN, gel pieces were equilibrated with 10 mM NH 4 HCO 3 containing porcine trypsin (12.5 ng/ml; Promega, Mannheim) on ice for 2 h. Excess trypsin solution was removed and hydrolysis was performed for 4 h at 37uC in 10 mM NH 4 HCO 3 . Digests were acidified with 5% trifluoroacetic acid (TFA) and the gel pieces were extracted twice with 0.1% TFA and then with 60% ACN/40% H 2 O/0.1% TFA followed by a two-step treatment using 100% ACN. Extractions were combined, concentrated by vacuum centrifugation, and desalted according to Rappsilber et al. [CITATION_2] .",
